The paper deals with distributed consensus algorithms, which are commonly studied in the systems and control community (cs.SY). The use of limited capacity channels and quantization also suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT). The analysis of the algorithm involves the theory of electric networks and random walks, which are topics in distributed computing (cs.DC) and network science (cs.NI). Finally, the use of Markov chains and convergence time analysis suggests a connection to mathematical analysis (cs.MA).
